            "creation_date": 1329173676,
            "body": "<p>The query part is where you specify a way to find you document, e.g: the <code>_id<\/code> or another unique field.<\/p>\n\n<p>In your example, it will look like this:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>ObjectId objectId = new ObjectId(\"4f39805d35919a2a7c7aba3e\");\nBasicDBObject queryObj = new BasicDBObject(\"_id\", objectId);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>(Maybe there's something missing about <code>ObjectId<\/code>, since I don't know Java.)<\/p>\n\n<p><strong>UPDATE<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<p>If you are searching for a specific <code>mouseLoc<\/code>, the <code>queryObj<\/code> will be the very <code>mouseLoc<\/code> object. (In JSON it would be <code>{ 'x': mouseX, 'y': mouseY }<\/code>.)<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 9269290,
            "question_id": 9268753,
            "last_edit_date": 1329174374
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/cafd689acd7039de41403b5e32692ceb?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 10378528,
